I don't/haven't used the menu functions that often, but you can achieve most of your desired effect through the following:
[code:1m0wl5xu]
msg (&quot;Available rooms&#58; &lt;br/&gt;Room &lt;u&gt;1&lt;/u&gt;                Room &lt;u&gt;2&lt;/u&gt;                Room &lt;u&gt;3&lt;/u&gt;&lt;br/&gt;Room &lt;u&gt;4&lt;/u&gt;                Room &lt;u&gt;5&lt;/u&gt;&quot;)
get input {
  switch (result) {
    case (1) {
      // Do choice 1 code here
    }
    case (2) {
      // Do choice 2 code here
    }
    case (3) {
      // And so on
    }
    case (4) {

    }
    case (5) {

    }
    default {
      msg (&quot;That's not a valid choice&#46;&quot;)
    }
  }
}[/code:1m0wl5xu]

Keep spacing and names uniform (I used 16 spaces between each name), and it'll look just fine. I suppose there are definitely better ways to do the above, but it's just about the simplest.
